Figure Element

<figure> is an element used to encapsulate media such as
 an image, illustration, diagram, code snippet, etc, 
 which is referenced in the main flow of the document.


<figure>
  <img src="overwatch.jpg"/>
</figure>



//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


Figcaption Element


<figcaption> is an element used to describe the media in 
the <figure> tag. Usually, <figcaption> will go inside 
<figure>.

<figure>
  <img src="overwatch.jpg">
  <figcaption>This picture shows characters from Overwatch.</figcaption>
</figure>